# Online multiplayer domain

`lib/online/` (~100 files) is the **highest regression-risk** area in Wordreapers. Room lifecycle involves opt-in rematch, presence, frozen round view, mid-round join, and voting — many non-obvious invariants.

## Before changing code

1. Read [`docs/online-multiplayer-rules.md`](../../docs/online-multiplayer-rules.md) for the state machine and navigation rules.
2. Read [`docs/decisions.md`](../../docs/decisions.md) for why key invariants exist.
3. Read [`docs/firebase_schema.md`](../../docs/firebase_schema.md) if you touch RTDB fields or read/write paths.
4. Search [`docs/known-issues.md`](../../docs/known-issues.md) for similar past bugs.

## Critical invariants (do not break casually)

- **Opt-in rematch** — next round starts only for players who pressed «Грати ще» or joined `waiting` after rematch.
- **Frozen round view** — players who did not opt in stay on their finished round UI; RTDB may already show the next round.
- **Presence** — `online` / `hasLeft` / `liveRoundPlayerUids` drive lobby visibility and round membership.
- **Mid-round join** — blind join into `playing`; `auto` x2 latches on at 3+ roster and never off mid-round; `off` never enables x2 for the round.

## After changing behavior

1. Update the relevant table in `docs/online-multiplayer-rules.md`.
2. Update `docs/firebase_schema.md` if schema or policies changed.
3. Add or update a test in `tests/` (many existing tests cover edge cases: `bootstrap-rematch-waiting`, `live-round-membership`, `mask-results-for-viewer`, etc.). For invariant changes, extend `tests/online-invariants.test.ts`.
4. If UX changed materially, update `docs/wordreapers_screens.html`.
5. Record non-trivial bug fixes in `docs/known-issues.md`.

Prefer pure functions in `lib/online/` over logic in screen components.
